🧾 Final Takeaway (Strong Closing Statement)

This project demonstrates that while multimodal transformer architectures are powerful, their success is fundamentally constrained by data scale, alignment quality, and training stability. The observed gap between classical models and deep multimodal systems reinforces a critical lesson: complexity must be justified by data. Future improvements should prioritize data-centric approaches, instruction tuning, and robust evaluation to unlock the true potential of end-to-end speech translation systems.
